{"id": "1442647324575928441", "channel_id": "1442647324575928441", "type": 0, "author_id": "180423498777362432", "author_name": "neckchin", "author_bot": false, "content": "Hey, trying to make a community tool for new players to reference, so that they can find what D-tide comps they can make based on the units that they have. Spent an hour or so prototyping. I haven't been able to find a way to get up to date D-tide leaderboard information without manually clicking through each player on the leaderboards, selecting each wave, and clicking \"copy lineup info\". \n\nSo, I think it'll be a limitation that players will have to manually paste in the comps that they know will work, or the community will need to compile a list. I've added a feature to batch-import, but it still feels clunky. I was wondering if the Morimens devs would be willing to open a API endpoint to fetch information about the people on the d-tide leaderboard, and their compositions for each wave. Or, if there is a chinese database for this already that we are not aware of. \n\nP.S. Additionally, the copy lineup information is a bit barebones, and only includes awakener name, wheel1 name, wheel2 name, and convenant. Are there plans to expand on this? It would be great if #epiphany is also available for wheels and characters. \n\n```\n@@o8xbn2ypyfyCx6ygxHSxp6gNKxCxAxXIWxwxbytkysyDHxmZxOixKrxgd@@Investigation Lineup\nKeeper: xxx（xxx） Team: -\n\nKaren, Duty's Gravitas, Sail of Providence, Re-evolution\nTawil, Eternal Requiem, Wheel Unseen, Dream of Medicine\nRyker, Hour of Fortune, Fate Roulette, Burial Ground's Sighs\nLotan, Whisper, Punishment, Burial Ground's Sighs\n\n@@mXWk5fxXxVxJx3xnxtxlSx5xZxT7ZxOixKrxgxAxXIWxwxbxAxXIWxwxbH@@\n```", "timestamp": "2025-11-24T22:45:25.270000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "☝️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 6}], "attachments": [{"id": "1442647325305733353", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/webp", "size": 70092, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1442647324575928441/1442647325305733353/image.png?ex=69fb1bc5&is=69f9ca45&hm=1449bb95810aea328254841305e081bbfdaf409df2ee02fd13af548db70cf75a&"}, {"id": "1442647325787951247", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 76473, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1442647324575928441/1442647325787951247/image.png?ex=69fb1bc5&is=69f9ca45&hm=a15521b76fde62bef54e46ce1df27a89b4cea6584fdc246d894d19d86defae5d&"}, {"id": "1442647326261776495", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 20781, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1442647324575928441/1442647326261776495/image.png?ex=69fb1bc5&is=69f9ca45&hm=729edf6262c640964aed345c3cf90afa4b2be3d6e5047ecfe3c7613ec1095745&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1442647324575928441", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Is there an open API for D-tide leaderboards?", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1181168197425172480"]}
